The paper deals with the representation and efficient determination of local upper bounds in multi-objective optimization, which involves computational geometry and optimization techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also discusses the use of local upper bounds in generating or approximating the nondominated set of an MOO problem, which relates to machine learning and artificial intelligence, hence cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also possible categories.
